# Audit: Scope and Module Boundaries

## 1. Scope compliance

Flag scope creep. V1 only:

- No V2/V3 features unless documented and approved
- No undocumented corrections
- No multi-tenant unless explicitly approved
- No AI/LLM in V1 invoice **decision** path
- No direct KSeF integration
- No panel manual retry unless explicitly approved
- No manual invoice creation endpoint

## 2. Module boundaries

| Layer | Allowed |
|-------|---------|
| `invoices` use-cases/services | Business logic, workflow order |
| Controllers | Thin HTTP; DTO shape; call use-cases |
| Repositories | Persist/read only |
| Integrations | External I/O; map provider payloads/results |
| n8n | Orchestration only — not critical financial logic |

Flag wrong-layer logic:

- Bitrix24 module must **not** decide invoice correctness
- Fakturownia integration must **not** decide whether invoice creation is allowed
- Business logic in controller, repository, or integration
